# Workflow Hooks

Consuming repos may install hooks from the **genai-agent-workflow** plugin (`hooks/hooks.json`
and `hooks/*.sh` in this plugin directory) or an equivalent `.cursor/hooks.json` layout in the
project to automate handoffs described in other workflow rules.

## subagentStop → doc-sync

When a subagent completes successfully, `subagentStop` hooks can return a `followup_message`
so the parent agent continues the chain without a manual reminder.

| After subagent | Hook script | Next step |
|----------------|-------------|-----------|
| `phase-executor` | `invoke-doc-sync-after-phase-executor.sh` | Invoke `doc-sync` (implementation sync) |
| `test-runner` | `invoke-doc-sync-after-test-runner.sh` | Invoke `doc-sync` (verification sync) |

Matchers use the subagent `name` from `.cursor/agents/<name>.mdc` (e.g. `phase-executor`).
If hooks do not fire, confirm the **Hooks** output channel and that `subagent_type` in the
event matches the matcher.

## Requirements

- `python3` on `PATH` (hook scripts parse stdin JSON)
- Copy `hooks.json` and make `*.sh` executable: `chmod +x .cursor/hooks/*.sh`
- Hooks complement — do not replace — `agent-workflow-boundaries.mdc` and agent prompts

## Disabling

Remove or comment out entries in `.cursor/hooks.json`, or omit the hooks directory when
installing this repo. Teams that prefer manual handoffs can rely on rules alone.
